match.title: Preview: Flamengo vs Atletico Mineiro - prediction, team news, lineups - Sports Mole
match.content: Headlines Football Previews Transfer News Tables Stats Centre F1 Tennis Cricket Rugby U NBA Betting More Home > Football > Flamengo [monks data] Brasileiro | Gameweek 17 Jul 28, 2025 at 12.30am UK Estadio Jornalista Mario Filho Flamengo 1 - 0 Atletico Mineiro FT Football Preview: Flamengo vs Atletico Mineiro - prediction, team news, lineups By Joshua Ojele Published: July 26 2025 | 08:01 Last updated: July 26 2025 | 15:27 © Iconsport Sports Mole previews Sunday's Brasileiro clash between Flamengo and Atletico Mineiro, including predictions, team news and possible lineups. Title hopefuls Flamengo will go in search of a third straight victory when they welcome Atletico Mineiro to the Maracana on Sunday in gameweek 17 of the 2025 Brasileiro season. Winning six of the most recent eight meetings, the hosts have dominated this fixture to a large degree against their visitors, who are without a win in two years. Match preview Back on the road for the first time since their 1-0 defeat to Santos, Flamengo looked set to suffer consecutive defeats before a late turnaround saw them down Red Bull Bragantino and leave Cicero de Souza Marques with all three points. Lucas Barbosa 's opener right after the interval was wiped out by Leo Pereira , after which Wesley popped up with an 85th-minute winner for Filipe Luis 's men in what could be his last game for the club amid transfer interest from Roma. Remaining hot on the heels of leaders Cruzeiro, O Mais Querido's tally of 33 points from 15 matches sees them sit just a point off top spot, having played one game fewer. Flamengo's title charge has been characterised by solidity at both ends of the pitch, as they currently boast the most goals scored in the division (29) as well as the fewest conceded (six). In the first of three clashes against the visitors over the next 10 days, this weekend's hosts are overwhelming favourites to come out on top on home turf, where their aggregate score across eight league matches so far currently stands at 20-1. Atletico Mineiro's rough July spell continued after they were knocked out of the Copa Sudamericana playoffs by Colombian outfit Bucaramanga on penalties in Friday's second leg at the MRV Arena. Alexi Stival 's men had claimed a 1-0 victory in the first leg but saw their advantage cancelled out by Jefferson Mena , forcing the tie to head to the luxury of spot kicks where Carlos Henao , Mena and Aldair Zarate all fluffed their lines. Prior to that, O Galo had lost both of their most recent two league outings clashes against Bahia and, most recently, Palmeiras, consequently dropping down to ninth in the standings, seven points shy of a Copa Libertadores spot. With little time to dwell on their recent continental heartbreak, Mineiro will need to pick themselves up and get back to winning ways on the domestic scene to avoid losing further ground on teams around them. Scoring the opening goal has often proven to be crucial in games involving Sunday's opponents, and the visitors could really do with striking the first blow against their hosts, who have been breached first in five of their last seven affairs. Flamengo Brasileiro form: W W W L W W Flamengo form (all competitions): D L W L W W Atletico Mineiro Brasileiro form: D D W W L L Atletico Mineiro form (all competitions): W W L W L L Team News Alex Sandro , Danilo and Gonzalo Plata are all nursing thigh injuries, ruling them out of contention for Flamengo. Allan and Nicolas de la Cruz are also expected to miss out for the home side due to a lack of match fitness alongside new arrival Saul Niguez (leg). Ayrton Lucas and Michael have both sat out each of the last three matches through leg and ankle injuries respectively, and the Brazilians are still a considerable way off returning to action. Cadu and Caio Maia are both nursing long-term knee injuries and remain without an appearance for Mineiro this term. Patrick Silva is facing an extended spell on the treatment table with a broken tailbone, while Guilherme Arana and Rubens are also sidelined for the away side.Â Flamengo possible starting lineup: Rossi; Varela, Pereira, Ortiz, Wesley; De Arrascaeta, Jorginho, E Araujo; Henrique, Pedro, L AraujoÂ Atletico Mineiro possible starting lineup: Everson; Paulista, Alonso, Lyanco, Natanael; Vera, Scarpa; Dudu, Gomes, Rony; Hulk We say: Flamengo 3-0 Atletico Mineiro Â Flamengo are dealing with several injury casualties at the moment but should still have enough in the tank to navigate the challenge of Atletico Mineiro. We can see the home side running riot en route to an emphatic victory at the end of the 90 minutes. match.title: Preview: Palmeiras vs Gremio - prediction, team news, lineups - Sports Mole
match.content: Headlines Football Previews Transfer News Tables Stats Centre F1 Tennis Cricket Rugby U NBA Betting More Home > Football > Palmeiras [monks data] Brasileiro | Gameweek 17 Jul 27, 2025 at 1am UK Allianz Parque Palmeiras 1 - 0 Gremio FT Football Preview: Palmeiras vs Gremio - prediction, team news, lineups By Adeyeye Oluwapelumi Published: July 24 2025 | 20:19 Last updated: July 24 2025 | 20:34 © Iconsport Sports Mole previews Sunday's Brasileiro clash between Palmeiras and Gremio, including predictions, team news and possible lineups. Aiming to continue their resurgent Brasileiro run, Palmeiras welcome Gremio to Allianz Parque this weekend in the 17th round of Brazil's top flight. Since returning from the FIFA Club World Cup, Abel Ferreira âs men have picked up seven points from a possible nine, and they now face a side yet to record a victory in their last four matches across all competitions. Match preview Palmeiras have firmly established themselves as a dominant force in recent seasons, having won the league title in two of the past three campaigns. After finishing as runners-up in the previous 2024, the Big Green find themselves just one spot lower in the current standings, with 29 points from 14 matches (W9, D2, L3), sitting five points behind leaders Cruzeiro, who have played two games more. Verdaoâs league campaign had paused for the 32-team tournament in the United States, where they exited at the quarter-final stage after a narrow 2-1 loss to eventual winners Chelsea, but Palmeiras have looked reinvigorated since resuming domestic duty. Having suffered back-to-back defeats prior to the Club World Cup, Palmeiras have returned to take a point in a 1-1 draw against Mirassol before sealing successive victories over Atletico Mineiro (3-2) and Fluminense (2-1), the latter coming in their most recent outing. Â Â Although Verdao will be hoping to secure a third straight victory, they have not exactly turned their home ground into a fortress, with only three wins from their seven league matches at Allianz Parque this season (D2, L2), but coming up against a side they have consistently outclassed in this fixture could tilt the odds in their favour. Â Â Indeed, Gremio have lost on each of their last four visits to this ground, three of which came in the top flight, including a narrow 1-0 defeat in the most recent meeting between the sides. The visitorsâ form on the road offers little cause for optimism either, with four defeats from seven league games played outside their home turf in 2025, though they did manage to come away with a point on their visit to Vasco da Gama in their latest top-flight outing. Â Mano Menezes âs side approach this clash off the back of a 1-1 draw with Alianza Lima, a result that confirmed their exit from the Copa Sudamericana following a 3-1 aggregate defeat. Â Â Gremio qualified for the continental competition after finishing 14th in the league last season, and they have managed only a slight improvement this time around, currently placed one spot higher with 17 points from 14 games (W4, D5, L7). Â Palmeiras Brasileiro form: W L L D W W Palmeiras form (all competitions): D W L D W W Gremio Brasileiro form: L W W D L D Gremio form (all competitions): D W L L D D Team News The absence of Estevao Willian has not had the adverse impact many feared, with Ferreira finding the right balance in attack through Facundo Torres , Felipe Anderson and Vitor Roque . Roque, in particular, will feel relieved after ending a two-month goal drought last time out, netting a 62nd-minute winner to seal a vital three points. However, Ferreira will be without winger Allan this weekend, after the substitute picked up a red card late in that same encounter. Â  Â Bruno Rodrigues , Figueiredo , Murilo Cerqueira and Paulinho also remain sidelined through injury, ruling them out of contention once again. Gremio will be without defenders Joao Pedro and Rodrigo Ely , both of whom are dealing with serious injuries â the former with a broken leg and the latter recovering from a cruciate ligament issue. Menezes will also have to make do without midfield duo Gustavo Cuellar (muscle) and Miguel Monsalve (dislocated shoulder). Â Palmeiras possible starting lineup: Weverton; Mayke, Fuchs, Gomez, Piquerez; Moreno, Evangelista; Anderson, Mauricio, Torres, Vitor Roque Gremio possible starting lineup: Volpi; Martins, Kannemann, Leonardo, Marlon; Villasanti, Dodi; Edenilson, Aravena, Pavon; Henrique We say: Palmeiras 2-0 Gremio Palmeiras are firm favourites heading into this clash given their current momentum and the psychological edge of recent home dominance in this fixture, and they should have enough quality to edge past a Gremio side still trying to find its feet.
